{"type":"text","timestamp":1775853745587,"sessionID":"ses_286dee775ffeBeM4v1TABWVMNZ","part":{"id":"prt_d7921aa73001vZb6THZRcXfipF","messageID":"msg_d7921a062001Z7aPI8wuUZFCTl","sessionID":"ses_286dee775ffeBeM4v1TABWVMNZ","type":"text","text":"Looking at the prompt more carefully, AR-013 is specifically about \"Redis 存储实现\" (Redis storage implementation) with the module `pkg/store`. The specs provided in `.sdd_prompt.md` are for the session store with both Redis and Valkey implementations.\n\nGiven that:\n1. AR-012 already has a proposal for \"Session Storage Interface Implementation\"\n2. AR-013 is specifically for \"Redis 存储实现\" (Redis Storage Implementation)\n3. The session-store/design.md and session-store/spec.md files already exist\n\nIt seems AR-013 should be focused on the actual Redis implementation (possibly just Redis, not both Redis and Valkey). Let me create the proposal for AR-013:","time":{"start":1775853745586,"end":1775853745586}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775853788930,"sessionID":"ses_286dee775ffeBeM4v1TABWVMNZ","part":{"id":"prt_d7921b5b4001T0L01VaCGAT1u7","messageID":"msg_d7921a062001Z7aPI8wuUZFCTl","sessionID":"ses_286dee775ffeBeM4v1TABWVMNZ","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_b9351fab1e2043bc8e968751","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-013/proposal.md","content":"# Proposal: Redis Storage Implementation (AR-013)\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement the Redis backend for the session storage interface in `pkg/store`, providing persistent sandbox metadata storage with indexed queries for garbage collection based on expiry and last-activity timestamps.\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe Redis storage implementation provides the primary backend for session persistence in the agentcube project. It enables:\n\n1. **Session persistence**: Store and retrieve sandbox information using Redis key-value storage\n2. **Garbage collection support**: Maintain sorted set indices for expiry and last-activity based cleanup\n3. **Production-ready storage**: Redis is the default and recommended backend for production deployments\n4. **Atomic operations**: Use Redis pipelines to ensure consistent index updates\n\nThis implementation is the focus of AR-013 and builds upon the interface defined in AR-012.\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n- `pkg/store/store_redis.go` - Redis implementation using `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9`\n- `sessionKey()` helper function for consistent key construction\n- `makeRedisOptions()` for environment variable parsing and client configuration\n- All `Store` interface methods implemented with Redis commands\n- Pipeline operations for atomic multi-command operations\n- Unit tests with mocked Redis client\n- Integration tests with real Redis instance (Docker-based)\n\n### Out of Scope\n\n- Valkey implementation (separate AR or combined with AR-012)\n- Alternative storage backends (etcd, Consul, etc.)\n- Redis cluster configuration and sharding strategies\n- Connection pooling tuning beyond default settings\n\n---\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | Redis client library |\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Structured logging (if needed for error reporting) |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | `SandboxInfo` type definitions |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store` | Store interface (from AR-012) |\n\n### Affected Components\n\n1. **Sandbox Orchestrator**: Will use `Storage()` to persist sandbox metadata\n2. **Garbage Collector**: Will use `ListExpiredSandboxes` and `ListInactiveSandboxes` for cleanup operations\n3. **Session Manager**: Will use `UpdateSessionLastActivity` for activity tracking\n4. **Configuration System**: Must provide `REDIS_ADDR` and `REDIS_PASSWORD` environment variables\n\n### Backward Compatibility\n\n- This is a new implementation of an existing interface\n- No breaking changes to the `Store` interface\n- Configuration via environment variables (no config file changes)\n\n### Risk Assessment\n\n| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|--------|------------|\n| Redis connection failures | Medium | High | `Ping()` method for health checks; connection retry in client library |\n| ZSET index inconsistency | Low | High | Atomic pipeline operations ensure all-or-nothing updates |\n| Password misconfiguration | Medium | High | Clear error messages; `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` escape hatch |\n| Memory bloat from orphaned ZSET members | Low | Medium | List methods tolerate missing keys; periodic cleanup recommended |\n| Pipeline command failures | Low | Medium | Check all pipeline results; return descriptive errors |\n\n---\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: Hash-Based Storage\n\n**Approach**: Store session data as Redis Hash instead of JSON string\n\n**Pros**:\n- Partial field updates without full serialization\n- More efficient for small field changes\n- Native Redis type\n\n**Cons**:\n- Complex nested structures (`EntryPoints` array) awkward in hashes\n- JSON marshaling already required for `SandboxInfo` type\n- Less portable if switching to other backends\n\n**Decision**: Use JSON string storage for simplicity and consistency.\n\n### Alternative 2: TTL-Only Expiration\n\n**Approach**: Rely solely on Redis native TTL instead of maintaining `session:expiry` ZSET\n\n**Pros**:\n- Simpler implementation\n- Automatic expiration handled by Redis\n- Reduced memory footprint\n\n**Cons**:\n- Cannot efficiently query \"sessions expiring before time X\"\n- Last-activity tracking still requires ZSET\n- Inconsistent semantics between expiry and activity indices\n\n**Decision**: Maintain explicit ZSET indices for efficient range queries required by garbage collection.\n\n### Alternative 3: Lua Script for Atomicity\n\n**Approach**: Use Lua scripts for `StoreSandbox` and `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` instead of pipelines\n\n**Pros**:\n- True atomic execution on Redis server\n- Reduced network round trips\n- More \"Redis-native\" approach\n\n**Cons**:\n- More complex code and debugging\n- Harder to test and maintain\n- Pipelines provide sufficient atomicity for this use case\n\n**Decision**: Use Redis pipelines for better code clarity and easier testing.\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Details\n\n### Redis Store Structure\n\n```go\ntype redisStore struct {\n    cli                  *redisv9.Client\n    sessionPrefix        string\n    expiryIndexKey       string\n    lastActivityIndexKey string\n}\n```\n\n### Key Patterns\n\n| Purpose | Key Pattern |\n|---------|-------------|\n| Session data | `session:{sessionId}` |\n| Expiry index | `session:expiry` |\n| Last activity index | `session:last_activity` |\n\n### Connection Configuration\n\n```go\nfunc makeRedisOptions() (*redisv9.Options, error) {\n    redisAddr := os.Getenv(\"REDIS_ADDR\")\n    if redisAddr == \"\" {\n        return nil, errors.New(\"REDIS_ADDR is required\")\n    }\n    \n    redisPassword := os.Getenv(\"REDIS_PASSWORD\")\n    passwordRequired := true\n    if v := os.Getenv(\"REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\"); strings.EqualFold(v, \"false\") {\n        passwordRequired = false\n    }\n    \n    if passwordRequired && redisPassword == \"\" {\n        return nil, errors.New(\"REDIS_PASSWORD is required (set REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false to disable)\")\n    }\n    \n    return &redisv9.Options{\n        Addr:     redisAddr,\n        Password: redisPassword,\n    }, nil\n}\n```\n\n### Method Implementation Summary\n\n| Method | Redis Commands | Notes |\n|--------|----------------|-------|\n| `Ping` | `PING` | Expect `PONG` response |\n| `GetSandboxBySessionID` | `GET session:{id}` | Return `ErrNotFound` on nil |\n| `StoreSandbox` | Pipeline: `SETNX`, `ZADD expiry`, `ZADD last_activity` | Validate non-nil and non-zero ExpiresAt |\n| `UpdateSandbox` | `SET key value XX` | Return error if key doesn't exist |\n| `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` | Pipeline: `DEL`, `ZREM expiry`, `ZREM last_activity` | Clean up all references |\n| `ListExpiredSandboxes` | `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:expiry -inf {before.Unix} LIMIT 0 limit` + pipeline GETs | Skip missing keys |\n| `ListInactiveSandboxes` | `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:last_activity -inf {before.Unix} LIMIT 0 limit` + pipeline GETs | Skip missing keys |\n| `UpdateSessionLastActivity` | `GET` (check exists), then `ZADD session:last_activity` | Return `ErrNotFound` if missing |\n| `Close` | `cli.Close()` | Close Redis connection |\n\n### Atomicity Guarantees\n\n- `StoreSandbox`: Pipeline ensures all-or-nothing for SETNX + ZADD + ZADD\n- `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`: Pipeline ensures all-or-nothing for DEL + ZREM + ZREM\n- `UpdateSandbox`: Single `SET XX` command is atomic\n\n### Error Handling\n\n- `redis.Nil` → `store.ErrNotFound`\n- Connection errors → wrapped with context\n- Pipeline errors → fail fast with descriptive message\n\n---\n\n## Configuration Reference\n\n### Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Notes |\n|----------|----------|---------|-------|\n| `REDIS_ADDR` | Yes | - | Host:port format (e.g., `localhost:6379`) |\n| `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Conditional | - | Required unless `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` |\n| `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | `true` | Case-insensitive boolean |\n| `STORE_TYPE` | No | `redis` | Must be `redis` or empty for this implementation |\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n1. **TestRedisStore_Ping_Success**: Mock `PING` returns `PONG`\n2. **TestRedisStore_GetSandboxBySessionID_NotFound**: Mock `GET` returns `nil`\n3. **TestRedisStore_StoreSandbox_NilRejected**: Validate input validation\n4. **TestRedisStore_StoreSandbox_Success**: Verify pipeline commands\n5. **TestRedisStore_UpdateSandbox_MissingKey**: Verify `SET XX` behavior\n6. **TestRedisStore_DeleteSandboxBySessionID_Success**: Verify cleanup\n7. **TestRedisStore_ListExpiredSandboxes_Empty**: Limit <= 0 returns nil\n8. **TestRedisStore_UpdateSessionLastActivity_NotFound**: Missing session\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n1. **TestRedisStore_Integration_FullLifecycle**: Full CRUD operations with real Redis\n2. **TestRedisStore_Integration_ConcurrentAccess**: Concurrent store/update/delete\n3. **TestRedisStore_Integration_IndexConsistency**: Verify ZSET consistency after operations\n4. **TestRedisStore_Integration_PasswordAuth**: Test with password authentication\n\n### Test Fixtures\n\n```go\nfunc newTestRedisStore() (*redisStore, func()) {\n    // Use testcontainers-go or dockertest for Redis container\n    // Return cleanup function\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `redisStore` struct implements all `Store` interface methods\n- [ ] Key patterns match spec: `session:`, `session:expiry`, `session:last_activity`\n- [ ] Pipeline operations used for `StoreSandbox` and `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`\n- [ ] `ErrNotFound` returned consistently for missing sessions\n- [ ] Environment variable parsing matches spec table\n- [ ] `makeRedisOptions()` validates required fields\n- [ ] All unit tests pass with mocked client\n- [ ] Integration tests pass with real Redis instance\n- [ ] Code coverage >= 80% for `store_redis.go`\n- [ ] Documentation includes usage examples\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- Interface Definition: `session-store/design.md`\n- Specification: `session-store/spec.md`\n- AR-012 Proposal: `changes/AR-012/proposal.md` (base interface work)\n- Redis Client Docs: https://github.com/redis/go-redis\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-013/proposal.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-013/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775853788916,"end":1775853788926}}}}
